olive oil
2 sprig Rosemary
4 clove Garlic
30 g butter
4 Orange Kumara
1 packet venison steak
2 bunch(es) baby broccoli
1 lemon
1 packet Red Wine Jus
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• See ‘Top Steak Tips’! (below left). Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Pick and finely chop rosemary and half the garlic.
• In a small microwave-safe bowl, place rosemary, chopped garlic and the
butter. Microwave until melted and fragrant, 10 second bursts.
• Cut each kūmara in half lengthways. Place kūmara half flat-side down on
a board between two wooden spoon handles (or chopsticks). Thinly slice
kūmara without cutting all the way through.
• Place on lined oven tray, flat side down and repeat with remaining kūmara.
Season with salt and pepper and drizzle with rosemary butter. Roast until
tender, 30-35 minutes.

• When kumara has 15 minutes remaining, season venison steak generously
with salt and pepper. Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle
of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, add venison and cook for 3-5 minutes on each side
(depending on thickness), or until cooked to your liking.
• Transfer to a plate, cover and rest for 5 minutes.
TIP: This will give you a medium steak. Cook for a little less if you like it rare, or a
little longer for well done.

• While steak is resting, trim baby broccoli and halve any thicker stalks
lengthways. Cut lemon into wedges. Thinly slice remaining garlic.
• Wipe out frying pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of
olive oil.
• Cook baby broccoli, until tender, 5-6 minutes. Add garlic and cook until
fragrant, 1 minute (cook in batches if needed).
• Season and add a generous squeeze of lemon juice.

• In a second small microwave-safe bowl, combine red wine jus and any
venison resting juices. Microwave until heated through, 30 seconds.
• Thinly slice steak.
• Bring venison steak, thyme hasselback kūmara and baby broccoli to the
table. Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese over baby broccoli.
• Serve with red wine jus and any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!